After talking with Secretary Mattis, we included new flexibility for @DeptofDefense to ensure that these funds were able to be spent in the smartest way possible while still maintaining stringent oversight.
By the time this agreement is enacted, @DeptofDefense will have around 5 months to spend the money. I was very concerned that this short time frame could lead to poor spending decisions.

We also funded programs to protect and defend Israel including: 
✔️Anti-tunneling initiatives; and 
✔️The Israeli cooperative missile defense programs.
Our military must be ready for future threats.  The @DeptofDefense must look five, ten and twenty years ahead to make sure we have the weapons systems we need.

✔️One carrier replacement,
✔️3 littoral combat ships,

The omnibus provides a total of $654 billion for fiscal year 2018. This is $23 billion above the president’s request, and $61 billion over last year.

Congress has finally delivered on the promise of tax reform, and I am proud to have supported this historic tax bill.
There has been a lot of mischaracterization of what this bill does, but the American people will know the truth when they start to see more money in their paychecks as early as February of next year.
Businesses will be able to immediately write off the full cost of new equipment to improve operations and enhance the skills of their workers.

This legislation delivers real relief to businesses by lowering the corporate tax rate to 21 percent, down from 35 percent. In fact, it reduces taxes on small businesses to the lowest they’ve been in 40 years.
It also allows Texans to write off up to $10,000 of their property taxes.

With this bill, the typical family of four earning the median family income of $73,000 will receive a tax cut of $2,059. The bill also expands the Child Tax Credit from $1,000 to $2,000 for single filers and married couples to help parents with the cost of raising children.
The bill nearly doubles the standard tax deduction and reduces loopholes, while preserving important tax breaks such as the teacher tax deduction for classroom expenses.
In addition, this legislation not only protects current American jobs but also encourages companies who have moved overseas to come home and bring jobs back to Texas.
Today, the House passed the most sweeping, pro-growth tax reform since President Reagan. These tax cuts will ensure Texans keep more of their hard earned money.
